abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump is now open to having a shorter impeachment trial in the Senate, two sources familiar with the situation said on Wednesday, after he initially proclaimed he wanted a full-blown, potentially lengthy hearing.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump is now open to having a shorter impeachment trial in the Senate, two sources familiar with the situation said on Wednesday, after he initially proclaimed he wanted a full-blown, potentially lengthy hearing.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump is now open to having a shorter impeachment trial in the Senate, two sources familiar with the situation said on Wednesday, after he initially proclaimed he wanted a full-blown, potentially lengthy hearing.
headline_main: Trump Now Open to Idea of Shorter Senate Trial: Sources
headline_print_headline: Trump Now Open to Idea of Shorter Senate Trial: Sources

abstract: A bipartisan group of lawmakers agreed to give troops a pay raise and the president his Space Force, while jettisoning a slew of measures that would have reined in the president’s war powers.
snippet: A bipartisan group of lawmakers agreed to give troops a pay raise and the president his Space Force, while jettisoning a slew of measures that would have reined in the president’s war powers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House on Wednesday passed a $738 billion military policy bill that would authorize the creation of the Space Force championed by President Trump as the sixth branch of the military and secure paid parental leave for more than two million federal workers.

abstract: In June, President Trump promised that millions of undocumented immigrants already in the country would be deported. That didn’t happen.
snippet: In June, President Trump promised that millions of undocumented immigrants already in the country would be deported. That didn’t happen.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Arrests and deportations of undocumented immigrants inside the United States dropped in the past year, according to government data released on Wednesday, a sharp contrast to the “millions” of deportations that President Trump promised this summer.

snippet: Edward O’Callaghan worked closely with Rod J. Rosenstein to oversee the Russia investigation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The primary liaison between the Justice Department and the special counsel’s office is set to step down at the end of the month, after helping oversee the department’s most consequential and controversial investigation in a generation.

abstract: The Sinclair group of local television stations said Wednesday it is dropping its commentary segments featuring Boris Epshteyn, former aide to President Donald Trump, in favor of a greater emphasis on local investigative journalism.
snippet: The Sinclair group of local television stations said Wednesday it is dropping its commentary segments featuring Boris Epshteyn, former aide to President Donald Trump, in favor of a greater emphasis on local investigative journalism.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Sinclair group of local television stations said Wednesday it is dropping its commentary segments featuring Boris Epshteyn, former aide to President Donald Trump, in favor of a greater emphasis on local investigative journalism.
headline_main: Sinclair Dumping Former Trump Aide Epshteyn's Commentaries
headline_print_headline: Sinclair Dumping Former Trump Aide Epshteyn's Commentaries

abstract: Legendary U.S. oilman Harold Hamm, who once called the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries a "toothless tiger," will step down as chief executive of Continental Resources and become its executive chairman, the company said on Wednesday.
snippet: Legendary U.S. oilman Harold Hamm, who once called the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries a "toothless tiger," will step down as chief executive of Continental Resources and become its executive chairman, the company said on Wednesd...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Legendary U.S. oilman Harold Hamm, who once called the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries a "toothless tiger," will step down as chief executive of Continental Resources and become its executive chairman, the company said on Wednesday.
headline_main: Continental Resources Founder Hamm to Step Down as CEO
headline_print_headline: Continental Resources Founder Hamm to Step Down as CEO

abstract: More than 2 million federal workers will get paid parental leave for the first time, for 12 weeks, following a birth or adoption, under U.S. legislation poised to pass the House of Representatives on Wednesday.
snippet: More than 2 million federal workers will get paid parental leave for the first time, for 12 weeks, following a birth or adoption, under U.S. legislation poised to pass the House of Representatives on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 2 million federal workers will get paid parental leave for the first time, for 12 weeks, following a birth or adoption, under U.S. legislation poised to pass the House of Representatives on Wednesday.
headline_main: U.S. Poised to Give Federal Workers 12 Weeks of Paid Parental Leave
headline_print_headline: U.S. Poised to Give Federal Workers 12 Weeks of Paid Parental Leave

abstract: The Senate has confirmed two conservative, Justice Department lawyers to posts on a California-based appeals court that President Donald Trump has tagged as a liberal bastion.

headline_main: Senate OKs Appeals Court Judges Over Home-State Opposition
headline_print_headline: Senate OKs Appeals Court Judges Over Home-State Opposition

abstract: U.S. Rep. Ted Lieu of California was recovering Wednesday following surgery in Washington to implant a heart stent after he experienced chest pains, his office said.
snippet: U.S. Rep. Ted Lieu of California was recovering Wednesday following surgery in Washington to implant a heart stent after he experienced chest pains, his office said.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — U.S. Rep. Ted Lieu of California was recovering Wednesday following surgery in Washington to implant a heart stent after he experienced chest pains, his office said.

headline_print_headline: Rep. Ted Lieu of California Recovering After Heart Procedure

abstract: U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrested fewer people during the 2019 budget year than last year, in part because resources were shifted to help handle the massive surge of migrants at the U.S.-Mexico border, the agency said Wednesday.
snippet: U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrested fewer people during the 2019 budget year than last year, in part because resources were shifted to help handle the massive surge of migrants at the U.S.-Mexico border, the agency said Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: DALLAS — U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrested fewer people during the 2019 budget year than last year, in part because resources were shifted to help handle the massive surge of migrants at the U.S.-Mexico border, the agency said Wednesday.
headline_main: ICE Arrested Fewer in 2019 as Resources Shifted to Border
headline_print_headline: ICE Arrested Fewer in 2019 as Resources Shifted to Border
